 Here are some tornado facts from the National Weather Service, Insurance Information Institute and news accounts: _Tornadoes can occur in any month, but are more frequent from April through June and between 3 and 6 p.m. _Most tornadoes track southwest to northeast, but their paths can spiral erratically. _The portion of a thunderstorm adjacent to large hail is where tornadoes are most likely to occur. _There were 32 tornado-related deaths reported in 1988, down from 59 in 1987 and well below the average of 99 a year. _Less than 2 percent of all tornadoes are classified as violent, with wind speeds of more than 200 mph and a path averaging 26 miles.
